  "text": "Archived tissue processing for aCGH. Fifteen 15-μm slices were cut for each patient from formalin fixed, paraffinembedded RP prostate tissue blocks. H&E stains were performed on 5-μm slices representative of the beginning and the end of the cut section. A single pathologist outlined areas of >80% tumor for macrodissection with a scalpel. DNA was extracted using the Puregene DNA isolation kit (Gentra Systems) as per the manufacturer's instructions. Phenol/chloroform extraction was done after the Gentra kit's final elution step. This kit has yielded good quality DNA from formalin fixed, paraffin-embedded material for aCGH in our laboratory [CITATION_1] 5) .",
